content.description: Two pitch route that starts from the anchors of How Homer Got His Groove Back.  Follow the line of bolts from the ledge to a ledge and belay.  Follow the wide crack from the belay ledge to the summit.
content.protection: Quickdraws for the first pitch, second pitch protects with a couple TCUs up to #3.  Wide gear optional.  Two bolt anchor at the top of the first pitch.  Gear anchor on the summit.
content.location: Top of How Homer Got His Groove Back.

content.description: The route on the left. A tricky start and then lots of crimpy moves as you head over to the anchors.
content.location: Located further along towards the far end of Gibraltar close to the trail

content.description: Route on the right. If the start is a little too tough for you, use the arete on the right and head up and reach over to the first bolt. The rest climbs much easier.
content.location: Located further along towards the far end of Gibraltar close to the trail

content.description: Follows a overhung right leaning crack system which enters a over hung blank face.
content.location: To the right of Flight from Urushiol (far left dihedral climb)

content.description:
This route shares top anchors and several bolts with Dr. Ceuse (10b).

Just stay in the dihedral.

The rock is kind of chossy, make sure your belayer stands at a safe distance as there is a very large (definitely bigger than a bread box) very loose chunk of rock 3/4 of the way up the route just waiting to fall down and kill someone.
content.location: Upon parking at Northrup Canyon Equestrian Area go south east from the parking area to the wall that is most likely in the shade, hike up toward the big pillar.

content.description: Climb the slab right of the arete.
content.location: This route is in the middle of the East Face of West Gibraltar Rock

content.description: Quality climbing up the left most dihedral. Technical stemming and high quality rock await. Jump on it!
Great sport route on edges and jugs up an overhanging wall to a dynamic finish.
content.location: East Side of Gibralter Rock up Northrup Canyon. Route starts up the gully on the lookers right side of Gibralter Rock.
